LEGAL NOTICE

Date: 12.01.2026

To,
The Chief Engineer,
Water Resources Department,
Government of Rajasthan, Jaipur

Subject: Demand for ₹42.50 Crore towards Geological Surprises, Design Changes, and Appointment of Arbitrator.

Sir,

We act on behalf of our client M/s. Rajasthan Construction Consortium regarding the Banas Dam Project.

The foundation excavation exposed massive un-weathered rock and swelling clay, which was completely different from the tender borehole logs (Type I). This constitutes "Unforeseeable Physical Conditions" under FIDIC Clause 4.12. Furthermore, the Department revised the spillway design mid-project, rendering the initial work redundant.

Our client has submitted claims totaling ₹42.50 Crore. The Department has failed to respond or make payment. 
We hereby give 15 days' notice to release the admitted amounts and grant a 12-month EOT, failing which we shall invoke Arbitration.

Yours faithfully,
Advocates for M/s Rajasthan Construction Consortium
